    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate focusing on the significant velocity advantage provided by **Mickey Moniak** and **Jose Caballero**. **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) secures the top spot in our rankings, benefiting from a pristine matchup against Holmes, G with a massive +14% platoon edge and favorable park factors. Similarly, **Jose Caballero** (69.65) is a high-upside play against Povich, whose L-handedness allows **Jose Caballero** to exploit his dynamic platoon advantage, even with a slight drag from his #7 lineup slot. We are also leaning heavily into **Austin Riley** (73.68) today; while he faces a LHP, the pairing with Quintana (5.47 xERA) and the park\u2019s positive hitting environment makes him our most efficient utility option, neutralizing the typical platoon risk. **Brice Turang** (72.12) remains essential as our primary engine for the scarce stolen base category, and despite a slight penalty for Irvin, J\u2019s ability to hold runners, his speed profile and #2 lineup position ensure he stays in the elite tier of our daily starters.\n\nOur toughest personnel decision involved **Josh Naylor** (43.14), who narrowly missed the starting cut. While **Josh Naylor** projected above the \"below floor\" threshold, the combination of a difficult matchup against Ragans and a negative park factor pushed him into the bench role behind higher-efficiency options like **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Seiya Suzuki**. Risk management remains a primary concern for today's lineup: **Corbin Carroll** and **Seiya Suzuki** are both battling a \"Wind In\" advisory that clipped their base projections, and while both remain in the starting nine, their actual output may deviate from the ATC projections if the air remains heavy. We continue to monitor the status of **Giancarlo Stanton** and **Max Muncy**, both of whom remain sidelined, while **Cole Young** remains on the bench, failing to meet our 40-point efficiency floor against the challenging Ragans matchup. We are currently navigating these decisions without the depth of **Carson Williams**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Kyle Karros**, **Luis Campusano**, or **Alex Freeland**, who remain monitored for future call-up or utilization potential.",
